{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of fiduciary duty by abusing their position as an accountant to misappropriate $25,000. While the court recognizes the personal financial pressure and the lack of a prior criminal record, embezzlement of this scale requires a term of incarceration to serve as a deterrent and to uphold the integrity of the profession. The defendant's proactive efforts to partially repay the stolen funds indicate remorse and a low risk of recidivism, which justifies a sentence on the lower end of the typical range for white-collar crimes of this magnitude.",
  "verdict": 8
}
